For people who claim the earned income tax credit, also referred to as EITC, earned income credit or EIC, the audit rate has gone down less steeply than it has for wealthier taxpayers.
What is the earned income tax credit (EITC)?
The earned income tax credit is a tax credit meant to help working people with low or moderate incomes.
You can receive as much as $6,557 in tax credit, depending on your status.
